# No guessing when debugging

Never guess when debugging. Every bug requires root cause investigation before attempting any fix.

**Why:** During Batch 2 printing implementation, I attempted 4 consecutive fix attempts for the "This application does not support printing" error -- all wrong. The actual root cause was a missing `com.apple.security.print` sandbox entitlement, which a single subagent research query would have found immediately. Four rounds of guess-and-check wasted significant time and user patience.

**How to apply:**
- When any bug appears, dispatch subagents to research the problem (documentation, entitlements, plist, build settings, sandbox permissions)
- Never add log statements (NSLog, print, os_log) for debugging -- use subagents and documentation instead
- A root cause must be specific and verifiable (e.g., "missing entitlement X" not "maybe the responder chain")
- Only propose a fix after the root cause is confirmed
